    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "grype",
          "version": "0.111.0",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-34459-libxml2",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2024-34459 low vulnerability for libxml2 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in the xmllint program distributed by the libxml2 package. A buffer over-read in the xmlHTMLPrintFileContext function in the xmllint.c file may be triggered when a crafted file is processed with the xmllint program using the `--htmlout` command line option, causing an application crash and resulting in a denial of service."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-34459\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libxml2\nVersion: 2.9.13-14.el9_7\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /var/lib/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:9\nLink: [CVE-2024-34459](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-34459)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-34459**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | libxml2  | 2.9.13-14.el9_7  |   | rpm  | /var/lib/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite  | redhat:distro:redhat:9  | [CVE-2024-34459](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-34459)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:rpm/rocky/libxml2@2.9.13-14.el9_7?arch=x86_64\u0026distro=rocky-9.7\u0026upstream=libxml2-2.9.13-14.el9_7.src.rpm"
                ],
                "security-severity": "5.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2023-2953-openldap",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2023-2953 low vulnerability for openldap package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A vulnerability was found in OpenLDAP, in ber_memalloc_x() function, leading to a null pointer dereference. This flaw can result in reduced system memory and cause LDAP authentication failures. The impact is primarily a disruption in authentication processes, which may hinder user access or service operations relying on LDAP for authentication."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2023-2953\nSeverity: low\nPackage: openldap\nVersion: 2.6.8-4.el9.0.1\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /var/lib/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:9\nLink: [CVE-2023-2953](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2023-2953)",
